		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<!-- wp:list {"ordered":true} -->
<ol id="sensei-quiz-list" class="wp-block-list"><!-- wp:list-item -->
<li>What is comment spam?<!-- wp:list -->
<ul class="wp-block-list"><!-- wp:list-item -->
<li>A feature to connect with readers</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item -->

<!-- wp:list-item -->
<li>Spammers posting comments to a website</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item -->

<!-- wp:list-item -->
<li>A way to manage spam on a website</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>
<!-- /wp:list --></li>
<!-- /wp:list-item -->

<!-- wp:list-item -->
<li>CAPTCHA is a technology used to tell robots and humans apart.<!-- wp:list -->
<ul class="wp-block-list"><!-- wp:list-item -->
<li>True</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item -->

<!-- wp:list-item -->
<li>False</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>
<!-- /wp:list --></li>
<!-- /wp:list-item -->

<!-- wp:list-item -->
<li>WordPress has built-in features to limit spam comments<!-- wp:list -->
<ul class="wp-block-list"><!-- wp:list-item -->
<li>True</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item -->

<!-- wp:list-item -->
<li>False</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>
<!-- /wp:list --></li>
<!-- /wp:list-item -->

<!-- wp:list-item -->
<li>You could avoid using an anti-spam plugin and instead rely solely on the built-in features of WordPress to mitigate spam.<!-- wp:list -->
<ul class="wp-block-list"><!-- wp:list-item -->
<li>True</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item -->

<!-- wp:list-item -->
<li>False</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>
<!-- /wp:list --></li>
<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>
<!-- /wp:list -->]]></content:encoded>
